WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.958
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

00:10.875 --> 00:12.125
[Thaddeus] <i>I cannot wait</i>

00:12.125 --> 00:14.875
to see the look on everyone's faces
when they see us

00:14.875 --> 00:16.625
return with the target.

00:18.083 --> 00:19.375
Maximus.

00:19.500 --> 00:21.458
[screams]

00:21.458 --> 00:22.875
- [grunts]
- [powering down]

00:22.875 --> 00:25.791
[Thaddeus] This stinky old head's
mine now!

00:25.791 --> 00:28.875
You don't think it's weird that we always
elect an overseer from Vault 31?

00:28.875 --> 00:31.833
[Betty] <i>Some of us will be
moving into Vault 32</i>

00:31.833 --> 00:33.916
<i>to start anew.</i>

00:33.916 --> 00:35.875
[Steph] <i>They killed my husband.</i>

00:35.875 --> 00:39.000
If your father were here, he--
he'd do the right thing.

00:39.000 --> 00:42.083
[Sebastian] <i>I'm telling you,
radicalism is sweeping through Hollywood.</i>

00:42.083 --> 00:43.708
You should come to a meeting.

00:43.708 --> 00:46.125
<i>You should learn the truth
about where your wife works.</i>

00:46.125 --> 00:47.416
[Miss Williams] <i>Mr. Howard?</i>

00:47.416 --> 00:49.458
I'm a big fan.

00:50.000 --> 00:53.583
Welcome to Vault 4.
Stay out of Level 12.

00:54.833 --> 00:56.708
[Maximus] <i>Where do you guys get
your power from?</i>

00:56.708 --> 00:58.791
[Birdie] I see you've found
our fusion core.

01:00.625 --> 01:02.750
[alarm blaring]

01:03.875 --> 01:05.125
- [hisses]
- [screams]

01:19.291 --> 01:21.291
[atmospheric music playing]

01:39.458 --> 01:41.458
♪ ♪

01:46.833 --> 01:48.833
[beeping]

02:09.166 --> 02:11.166
♪ ♪

02:32.250 --> 02:34.791
[Adam] Sandra, we're home.

02:35.833 --> 02:37.833
[wind whistling]

02:44.541 --> 02:46.541
[dark music playing]

02:52.166 --> 02:53.375
Sandra?

03:08.833 --> 03:10.833
[footsteps approach]

03:14.666 --> 03:16.291
[Ghoul] Thank you, darling.

03:18.666 --> 03:20.625
Oh, wait.

03:20.625 --> 03:22.916
You thought...?

03:25.083 --> 03:27.083
[laughs]

03:29.208 --> 03:30.541
Come on, now.

03:30.541 --> 03:33.250
Sandra, wait outside.

03:37.916 --> 03:40.541
Lead farming, huh?

03:40.541 --> 03:45.583
Why, hell, I probably still got
some of your lead in me somewhere.

03:47.208 --> 03:50.041
[sighs] But today...

03:52.041 --> 03:53.833
...I'm just looking for information.

03:53.833 --> 03:56.291
I'll tell you anything,

03:56.291 --> 03:58.958
as long as you leave us in peace.

03:58.958 --> 04:02.875
Say, am I out of date,

04:02.875 --> 04:05.375
or did I hear you had three kids?

04:08.250 --> 04:11.000
I had an older son, but he's gone.

04:11.000 --> 04:14.750
He took up with that madwoman
in the hills two years ago.

04:14.750 --> 04:16.958
We haven't heard from him since.

04:16.958 --> 04:19.000
Hmm.

04:21.000 --> 04:23.916
There's always some new little faction,
ain't there?

04:23.916 --> 04:27.166
Brand-new team of believers
with their own dumbass ideas

04:27.166 --> 04:29.833
about how they gonna save the world.

04:30.916 --> 04:35.750
What did you say the name
of your eldest was?

04:37.916 --> 04:39.333
Was it Roofus?

04:42.000 --> 04:44.541
- I didn't say--
- That must make you Tommy.

04:47.541 --> 04:49.583
What did you do?

04:49.583 --> 04:52.166
- What is that envelope?
- [Ghoul] Well, you see, daddy-o...

04:52.166 --> 04:54.666
now, from what I can tell...
[clears throat]

04:54.666 --> 04:58.625
...Old Roofus got Tommy here mixed up
with that madwoman, too.

04:58.625 --> 05:00.250
Now, according to this,

05:00.250 --> 05:04.291
Roofus sent Tommy
a stash of caps to pay a courier

05:04.291 --> 05:09.375
for "the safe transport
of an Enclave defector"

05:09.375 --> 05:13.500
to that very same madwoman in the hills.

05:13.500 --> 05:15.708
Moldaver.

05:15.708 --> 05:18.125
But my problem is,

05:18.125 --> 05:21.333
by the time I got this letter
off your brother,

05:21.333 --> 05:24.000
it was a little bit hard to read.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
[tense music playing]

05:26.000 --> 05:29.625
For some reason,
I just can't make out her location.

05:29.625 --> 05:32.208
Now, you give me that location,

05:32.208 --> 05:34.916
and I'll be on my way.

05:37.125 --> 05:38.833
[whispers] I'm sorry.

05:38.833 --> 05:40.541
Tell him, son.

05:41.791 --> 05:43.000
Just tell him.

05:44.041 --> 05:45.833
[Tommy] I didn't want to spend my life
digging through dirt.

05:45.833 --> 05:48.083
I want to build something,
and we have the chance--

05:48.083 --> 05:49.500
[Adam] Tell him what he wants to know!

05:49.500 --> 05:51.125
Or else he's gonna kill us all!

05:51.125 --> 05:54.208
Including your little sister.

05:56.750 --> 05:58.750
Huh.

06:06.166 --> 06:08.125
[Tommy] She's...

06:08.125 --> 06:10.250
she's at the Observatory.

06:10.250 --> 06:12.208
[exhales]

06:13.708 --> 06:16.750
Now, please, leave us.

06:18.791 --> 06:20.208
[exhales]

06:20.208 --> 06:22.083
[dark music playing]

06:22.083 --> 06:24.458
So, what you think, Tommy?

06:24.458 --> 06:27.125
Am I really walking out of here today,
or are you gonna try and draw on me

06:27.125 --> 06:29.833
for what I did to your big brother?

06:32.375 --> 06:35.583
- He won't.
- [Ghoul] Maybe not today,

06:35.583 --> 06:38.541
but maybe someday.

06:47.416 --> 06:48.875
Tommy!

06:48.875 --> 06:50.083
[exhales]

06:50.083 --> 06:52.166
[somber music playing]

07:19.458 --> 07:21.458
♪ ♪

07:26.916 --> 07:28.958
[Miss Williams] <i>What is it
about California,</i>

07:28.958 --> 07:31.958
<i>that we all came to this place?</i>

07:33.125 --> 07:35.208
[inhales deeply]

07:37.916 --> 07:40.458
[Miss Williams] Maybe it's the sunshine.

07:40.458 --> 07:43.125
Maybe it's the friendly people.

07:43.125 --> 07:47.791
When you think of the promise
of the American Dream,

07:47.791 --> 07:50.708
you think of California.

07:50.708 --> 07:54.083
But it is just a dream. It's not real.

07:54.083 --> 07:59.250
We were told the atom bomb
meant the end of war.

08:00.250 --> 08:01.750
That didn't work out, did it?

08:01.750 --> 08:04.708
We were told
America's always getting better,

08:04.708 --> 08:07.500
it's always moving toward a better future.

08:07.500 --> 08:11.666
But the future is getting closer,
and we can see it.

08:11.666 --> 08:16.291
Their "better future" is a cliff's edge.

08:16.291 --> 08:19.250
And it's coming up fast, isn't it?

08:19.250 --> 08:22.125
- [sighs]
- These soldiers
that we're fighting abroad,

08:22.125 --> 08:24.833
their families,
we have more in common with them

08:24.833 --> 08:28.041
than we do with the people
here in power, the real enemy.

08:28.041 --> 08:29.666
That's about all the horseshit
I can take.

08:29.666 --> 08:31.500
Coop. Coop, come on.

08:31.500 --> 08:33.541
- [indistinct whispers]
- Mr. Howard?

08:33.541 --> 08:35.875
- [sighs]
- I'm sorry, I didn't hear what you said.

08:35.875 --> 08:38.291
I said that, um...

08:38.291 --> 08:40.833
this is about all the horseshit
I can take.

08:40.833 --> 08:44.208
- [murmuring]
- I didn't realize
that America's favorite gunslinger

08:44.208 --> 08:47.375
- was so sensitive.
- [soft laughter]

08:47.375 --> 08:50.875
I have my principles,
Miss Williams, that's all.

08:50.875 --> 08:54.666
Uh-huh. And those principles of yours...

08:54.666 --> 08:58.500
how much did Vault-Tec pay
to take them off your hands?

09:00.458 --> 09:02.000
Well, this is America.

09:02.000 --> 09:03.625
Everybody has a sponsor,

09:03.625 --> 09:06.375
and, uh, I'm not ashamed to earn a living.

09:06.375 --> 09:08.333
[Miss Williams] Vault-Tec is
the largest company in America.

09:08.333 --> 09:12.250
There's a lot of money
in selling the end of the world.

09:12.250 --> 09:14.625
Well, I'm sure there's a lot of money
in selling a political ideology

09:14.625 --> 09:16.333
- that ends in breadlines.
- [woman] Fascist.

09:16.333 --> 09:19.416
Okay, uh, sorry, this was a mistake.
We'll be leaving.

09:19.416 --> 09:23.291
Oh, no, I'm-I'm quite glad
you brought Mr. Howard today.

09:24.916 --> 09:27.208
You see, it happens

09:27.208 --> 09:29.958
that I know your wife.

09:29.958 --> 09:32.416
And perhaps a side of her you don't.

09:32.416 --> 09:34.500
[contemplative music playing]

09:36.166 --> 09:37.791
[chuckles]

09:39.958 --> 09:41.083
How do you know my wife?

09:41.083 --> 09:43.708
My research company
was acquired by her division.

09:43.708 --> 09:48.041
We were developing this kind of technology
that's... difficult to monetize.

09:48.041 --> 09:51.041
Cold fusion. Infinite energy.

09:51.041 --> 09:53.291
That's what I was
on the verge of achieving

09:53.291 --> 09:57.583
when Vault-Tec swept in and bought up
every company I'd ever worked for.

09:57.583 --> 09:59.083
Every one of them?

09:59.083 --> 10:02.458
So, what are you, a millionaire communist?

10:02.458 --> 10:04.541
Hypocrisy is like violence in your movies.

10:04.541 --> 10:06.958
If you only let the bad guys use it,
the bad guys win.

10:06.958 --> 10:09.791
Yeah? I, uh, I got
a little showbiz secret for you.

10:09.791 --> 10:12.333
A good bad guy doesn't
see themselves as the bad guy.

10:12.333 --> 10:16.750
America has been locked in a resource war
for over a decade.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.666
Vault-Tec bought the means
to end that war,

10:19.666 --> 10:23.625
the same war you fought in,
so they could put it on the shelf.

10:23.625 --> 10:26.083
All because it didn't fit
into their business model.

10:26.083 --> 10:30.166
I want your help in getting it back.

10:37.250 --> 10:39.791
- [Cooper] What is it?
- It's a listening device.

10:39.791 --> 10:42.875
A listening device. You...

10:42.875 --> 10:44.625
you want me to spy on my wife?

10:45.666 --> 10:47.250
[soft chuckle]

10:55.416 --> 10:58.083
- Good luck with the revolution.
- You can keep it.

10:58.083 --> 10:59.708
As a token.

11:01.333 --> 11:03.708
I'm not a communist, Mr. Howard.

11:03.708 --> 11:08.916
That's just a dirty word they use
to describe people who aren't insane.

11:25.625 --> 11:27.625
♪ ♪

11:37.291 --> 11:39.291
[eerie music playing]

11:46.666 --> 11:49.208
[monitor beeping steadily]

11:50.291 --> 11:52.166
We let you into our home.

11:52.166 --> 11:55.291
Tended to your wounds,
gave you food and water.

11:55.291 --> 11:57.541
But you had to go to Level 12.

11:57.541 --> 12:00.458
I saw what you were doing
to those poor women.

12:00.458 --> 12:03.625
You're experimenting on them.
It's... it's sick.

12:03.625 --> 12:05.625
- She needs to see the holotape.
- [sighs]

12:05.625 --> 12:08.458
All right. Play the tape.

12:11.291 --> 12:13.500
<i>[panting] Okay.</i>

12:13.500 --> 12:15.500
<i>[Cassandra yelps]</i>

12:15.500 --> 12:17.375
What is this?

12:17.375 --> 12:20.125
- Your history.
- [Lloyd] <i>Overseer Hawthorne,</i>

12:20.125 --> 12:21.666
<i>final log entry.</i>

12:21.666 --> 12:23.666
<i>At this point,
it would be irrational of me</i>

12:23.666 --> 12:26.166
<i>not to acknowledge that these may be</i>

12:26.166 --> 12:28.000
<i>- my last words.
- [crash]</i>

12:28.000 --> 12:30.958
<i>But despite our results here,</i>

12:30.958 --> 12:33.916
<i>I want to reiterate that a society
governed by scientists</i>

12:33.916 --> 12:37.333
<i>- Honey! Hey!
- really is the ideal social structure.
- [pounding on door]</i>

12:37.333 --> 12:41.500
<i>What happened here
should not be used as a case study</i>

12:41.500 --> 12:44.500
for what happens when scientists
are given unregulated control.

12:44.500 --> 12:46.458
- Lloyd, gimme a little help!
- And-and--

12:46.458 --> 12:47.916
and-and hybridizing humans

12:47.916 --> 12:50.958
with radioactive-resistant species
still has potential.

12:50.958 --> 12:52.916
<i>[thudding]</i>

12:52.916 --> 12:54.583
<i>Our test subjects were</i>

12:54.583 --> 12:56.625
less compliant than we expected.

12:56.625 --> 12:58.208
[creature roars]

12:59.208 --> 13:00.625
[dramatic music playing]

13:00.625 --> 13:03.291
- [screaming]
- Cassandra! Oh, no!

13:04.666 --> 13:07.208
- No, no, no! [shouts]
- [creature growling]

13:07.208 --> 13:08.875
[screams] No!

13:17.333 --> 13:19.333
<i>[static]</i>

13:24.083 --> 13:25.083
<i>[static stops]</i>

13:25.083 --> 13:27.458
[sniffles] Sorry, I haven't, uh,

13:27.458 --> 13:29.583
seen that footage in a long time.

13:31.416 --> 13:32.708
But it's a stirring reminder

13:32.708 --> 13:35.541
of what this place is all about.

13:36.583 --> 13:39.208
I-I don't understand, I...

13:39.208 --> 13:42.291
In the lab, I-I saw your doctors--

13:42.291 --> 13:44.291
Trying to ease the pain of the poor souls

13:44.291 --> 13:47.041
your people lured into this place.

13:47.041 --> 13:49.500
His ancestors were used as lab rats

13:49.500 --> 13:52.333
by the original residents of Vault 4.

13:52.333 --> 13:54.625
- Until the lab rats rebelled.
- [Benjamin] The, uh,

13:54.625 --> 13:58.625
creature in the video was actually
my Great-Uncle Peter on my mom's side.

14:01.500 --> 14:03.708
I'm so sorry.

14:03.708 --> 14:05.541
I...

14:05.541 --> 14:10.500
I had no idea the original vault dwellers
here were so... so weird.

14:10.500 --> 14:13.458
I mean, my vault's not like this.

14:14.541 --> 14:18.041
What was the experiment in 33?

14:18.041 --> 14:21.750
W-Well, there is no experiment.

14:21.750 --> 14:24.333
[tense music playing]

14:25.875 --> 14:28.708
Your ignorance cannot excuse your cruelty.

14:28.708 --> 14:30.958
You have infected our home with violence

14:30.958 --> 14:33.916
and now you must pay the price.

14:36.375 --> 14:37.458
[Lucy] No!

14:37.458 --> 14:40.291
Please. Please, I'm a good person.

14:40.291 --> 14:42.125
[grunting]

14:42.125 --> 14:44.000
- [♪ Jack Shaindlin: "I'm Tickled Pink"
playing on TV]
- <i>♪ I'm tickled pink ♪</i>

14:44.000 --> 14:47.375
<i>♪ That things are rosy ♪</i>

14:47.375 --> 14:49.041
- <i>♪ And skies are blue ♪</i>
- [Lucy] Please!

14:49.041 --> 14:52.083
- <i>♪ Once again ♪</i>
- Please let me go. Let me go!

14:52.083 --> 14:54.166
[percussive music playing]

15:06.416 --> 15:08.416
[♪ Merle Travis: "Sixteen Tons"]

15:11.958 --> 15:13.958
[panting]

15:15.250 --> 15:17.250
<i>♪ Some ♪</i>

15:17.250 --> 15:20.333
- <i>♪ People say a man is made out of mud ♪</i>
- [CX404 barking]

15:20.333 --> 15:24.333
<i>♪ But a poor man's
made out of muscle and blood ♪</i>

15:24.333 --> 15:27.916
<i>♪ Muscle and blood
and skin and bones ♪</i>

15:27.916 --> 15:31.458
<i>♪ With a mind that's weak
and a back that's strong ♪</i>

15:31.458 --> 15:35.166
<i>♪ You load 16 tons
and what do you get? ♪</i>

15:35.166 --> 15:38.083
- <i>♪ You get another day
older and deeper in debt...</i>
- [sighs]

15:38.083 --> 15:39.250
Are you done?

15:39.250 --> 15:42.208
<i>♪ St. Peter, don't you call me
'cause I can't go ♪</i>

15:42.208 --> 15:45.791
- <i>♪ I owe my soul to the company store ♪</i>
- Okay, okay, here we go.

15:45.791 --> 15:49.583
[gasps]

15:49.583 --> 15:51.541
[groans]

15:52.666 --> 15:55.166
Oh, shit.

15:55.166 --> 15:57.375
I'm gonna fucking die.

15:57.375 --> 16:01.375
Ow, hey! That's my foot,
it's not food, okay?

16:02.708 --> 16:04.083
You know what?

16:04.083 --> 16:07.208
If you were a person, you wouldn't
have any friends, you realize that?

16:07.208 --> 16:08.541
- [whines]
- [sighs]

16:09.833 --> 16:12.291
Okay, I got to reevaluate here.

16:12.291 --> 16:13.666
What do I need, what do I need?

16:13.666 --> 16:15.958
This fucking stupid thing.
Oh, you want this too, huh?

16:15.958 --> 16:19.625
Everybody wants this.
Guess what? It's mine.

16:19.625 --> 16:21.458
You think everything's for you.

16:21.458 --> 16:24.041
It's pretty selfish, actually,
you know that?

16:24.041 --> 16:26.708
Bite what you want to bite,
go where you want to go.

16:26.708 --> 16:29.291
It's always something.

16:29.291 --> 16:30.875
Okay.

16:30.875 --> 16:32.791
Oh, hell yeah.

16:32.791 --> 16:34.500
You can't eat this.

16:35.708 --> 16:36.875
[sighs]

16:38.375 --> 16:41.375
[intriguing music playing]

16:43.625 --> 16:45.000
You know what?

16:46.000 --> 16:47.333
[grunts]

16:48.083 --> 16:50.583
Oh, yeah, this is great.

16:50.583 --> 16:52.541
Lot of space.

16:52.541 --> 16:54.208
You're a loose cannon, all right?

16:54.208 --> 16:56.875
This is a very important mission
and I can't have you jeopardizing it.

16:56.875 --> 16:59.375
It's bigger than you.
It's bigger than all of us.

17:00.833 --> 17:03.541
[imitates beeping sounds]

17:03.541 --> 17:05.375
- Great.
- [whining]

17:05.375 --> 17:08.000
Oh, see? You got a little window
and everything.

17:08.125 --> 17:10.250
You'll be fine.

17:10.250 --> 17:12.916
[scratching]

17:13.958 --> 17:15.000
You can breathe in there, right?

17:16.875 --> 17:19.083
All right, got a radio tower to find.

17:19.083 --> 17:23.041
Got to contact the Brotherhood,
get them this head,

17:23.041 --> 17:25.125
- and get me some glory.
- [choppy, indistinct radio chatter]

17:30.583 --> 17:33.000
[all chanting indistinctly]

17:33.000 --> 17:36.375
[Birdie] We are all survivors here.

17:36.375 --> 17:38.125
- Lucky enough to have found
- [grunting]

17:38.125 --> 17:40.500
this sanctum of peace.

17:40.500 --> 17:42.125
Of tolerance.

17:42.125 --> 17:44.833
It doesn't matter

17:44.833 --> 17:47.541
- where you come from or what you believe.
- [grunting]

17:47.541 --> 17:50.125
You deserve safety.

17:54.083 --> 17:55.333
- [can clatters]
- [woman sneezes]

17:56.291 --> 17:57.458
Unless...

17:57.458 --> 18:00.000
[ominous music playing]

18:03.666 --> 18:06.125
...you threaten that peace.

18:20.041 --> 18:22.666
For causing harm

18:22.666 --> 18:25.250
to a fellow survivor,

18:25.250 --> 18:29.583
you are hereby sentenced to death...

18:29.583 --> 18:30.500
[whimpers]

18:30.500 --> 18:34.083
...by banishment to the surface!

18:34.083 --> 18:36.166
[gentle sawing]

18:49.375 --> 18:50.833
It's almost there.

18:52.750 --> 18:55.458
Need to get that sharpened, please.
[clears throat]

18:57.083 --> 18:58.958
[straining]

19:00.000 --> 19:01.166
[grunts]

19:01.166 --> 19:02.625
[cheering]

19:02.625 --> 19:04.916
[triumphant music playing]

19:04.916 --> 19:06.375
Yeah! [whoops]

19:09.791 --> 19:13.458
You're just... letting me go?

19:14.708 --> 19:18.541
Well, that's certainly
an optimistic perspective.

19:18.541 --> 19:21.916
You'll be killed almost immediately
on the surface

19:21.916 --> 19:24.208
by Lord knows what.

19:24.208 --> 19:27.333
That's why we're giving you
two weeks of supplies to take with you.

19:27.333 --> 19:28.458
- Thank you, Cathy.
- [Cathy] Sure.

19:28.458 --> 19:31.208
After that, you are on your own, Goosey.

19:32.208 --> 19:34.541
Uh...

19:34.541 --> 19:36.125
That's, uh...

19:37.416 --> 19:40.708
That's... really nice of you guys.

19:40.708 --> 19:42.666
Okay, and now it is time

19:42.666 --> 19:45.125
to be moving along.

19:46.125 --> 19:47.916
Can I just ask you one thing?

19:47.916 --> 19:51.291
Obviously, someone will carry the supplies
to the surface for you.

19:51.291 --> 19:54.000
My friend really likes it here.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.958
And he's a good person.

19:55.958 --> 19:59.833
He deserves to be somewhere nice and safe,

19:59.833 --> 20:01.333
like this.

20:01.333 --> 20:03.666
<i>I know that I'm not really</i>

20:03.666 --> 20:07.666
<i>in the position to be asking favors.
[chuckles] But...</i>

20:07.666 --> 20:09.333
[suspenseful music playing]

20:12.791 --> 20:14.250
...can he stay?

20:15.625 --> 20:17.791
[crowd gasping]

20:21.625 --> 20:24.000
[automated voice on P.A.] <i>Backup power
initiated.</i>

20:24.000 --> 20:26.083
[soaring music playing]

20:35.208 --> 20:37.833
[Maximus] [distorted] Let her go!

20:37.833 --> 20:40.875
- [♪ The Platters: "Only You"]
- <i>♪ Only you ♪</i>

20:42.541 --> 20:46.166
<i>♪ Can make all this world ♪</i>

20:46.166 --> 20:48.083
- <i>♪ Seem bright ♪</i>
- [muffled] Titus, stop!

20:49.583 --> 20:52.541
<i>♪ Only you ♪</i>

20:55.208 --> 20:56.958
<i>♪ Can make ♪</i>

20:56.958 --> 20:59.916
<i>♪ The darkness bright ♪</i>

21:01.791 --> 21:04.000
<i>♪ Only you ♪</i>

21:04.000 --> 21:07.916
<i>♪ And you alone ♪</i>

21:07.916 --> 21:13.000
<i>♪ Can thrill me like you do ♪</i>

21:13.000 --> 21:14.875
Titus, stop.

21:16.208 --> 21:17.625
They're letting me go.

21:19.375 --> 21:20.458
Really?

21:20.458 --> 21:21.875
Yeah.

21:23.333 --> 21:24.833
Oops.

21:26.916 --> 21:28.416
Sorry.

21:30.000 --> 21:32.791
- Somebody maybe check on him.
- [groaning]

21:32.791 --> 21:34.875
["Bossa Angela" playing on speakers]

21:45.583 --> 21:47.333
What?

21:49.125 --> 21:51.375
We stole their fusion core.

21:51.375 --> 21:53.416
Well, yeah, but...

21:55.416 --> 21:57.666
You know, I needed it for the armor.

21:57.666 --> 21:59.375
Well, without their fusion core,
their auxiliary power

21:59.375 --> 22:01.750
will only last a few days, and...

22:01.750 --> 22:03.083
and then what?

22:05.166 --> 22:08.083
No... No.

22:08.083 --> 22:09.708
- Yes.
- No.

22:09.708 --> 22:11.875
Giving it back is the right thing to do.

22:11.875 --> 22:14.000
Without the fusion core,
this armor is useless.

22:14.000 --> 22:15.250
I can't be a knight.

22:15.250 --> 22:16.666
Well...

22:16.666 --> 22:19.333
you can't be a knight
by stealing from people either.

22:19.333 --> 22:21.791
Yeah, but I can help people
with this armor.

22:21.791 --> 22:23.708
- [sighs]
- All right?

22:23.708 --> 22:26.166
You, for example. I want to help you.

22:26.166 --> 22:29.208
You really want give them
their fusion core back

22:29.208 --> 22:30.875
if it means you don't get your dad?

22:32.791 --> 22:36.041
If my dad found out
that I destroyed an entire community

22:36.041 --> 22:37.875
to save him...

22:41.541 --> 22:43.208
...that'd break his heart.

22:50.333 --> 22:51.833
I can't.

22:55.583 --> 22:57.583
[melancholy music playing]

23:03.208 --> 23:05.208
[armor powers down]

23:18.458 --> 23:20.458
♪ ♪

23:26.041 --> 23:28.041
Come on.

23:49.416 --> 23:51.416
♪ ♪

23:58.750 --> 24:00.333
[alert blares]

24:00.333 --> 24:02.083
[janitor] Thank you!

24:08.041 --> 24:10.291
Thinking 'bout those oysters?

24:10.291 --> 24:12.375
Mm-hmm.

24:28.791 --> 24:31.458
We don't have oysters in my vault.

24:32.583 --> 24:34.666
We have canned tuna.

24:35.666 --> 24:38.041
[chuckles ] But if you like oysters,

24:38.041 --> 24:40.458
I'm pretty sure you'll like canned tuna.

24:42.083 --> 24:44.083
[chuckles softly]

24:47.791 --> 24:51.166
I was supposed to marry a stranger
from another vault.

24:52.250 --> 24:55.958
It didn't turn out so good.

24:55.958 --> 24:59.250
I don't have the best luck
when it comes to strangers.

25:02.833 --> 25:04.750
But...

25:04.750 --> 25:06.541
Titus...

25:07.750 --> 25:10.708
I can honestly say

25:10.708 --> 25:12.166
you are the best stranger

25:12.166 --> 25:14.916
that I've ever met.

25:14.916 --> 25:18.833
You're a good person, Titus.

25:18.833 --> 25:22.000
And if you wanted to,

25:22.000 --> 25:24.708
when all of this is over, you could come

25:24.708 --> 25:27.791
and live with us in Vault 33.

25:27.791 --> 25:29.875
[tranquil music playing]

25:33.875 --> 25:35.375
With me.

25:45.125 --> 25:46.583
There's something I should tell you.

25:46.583 --> 25:48.125
Just say yes.

25:48.125 --> 25:50.583
My name isn't Titus. It's Maximus.

25:50.583 --> 25:54.583
Titus is the name of the knight
who owned this suit before me.

25:59.083 --> 26:02.666
He was threatening me, so instead
of helping him I watched him die.

26:02.666 --> 26:05.916
And I took his armor and I lied to you.

26:08.750 --> 26:11.875
So, all that stuff you were saying,
you know, about, um,

26:11.875 --> 26:14.125
about me being a good person...

26:27.958 --> 26:31.458
I just threw acid
in an innocent man's face.

26:31.458 --> 26:33.750
And I've only been up here two weeks.

26:36.458 --> 26:38.208
The wasteland sucks.

26:42.291 --> 26:45.166
Yeah. Sometimes.

26:49.666 --> 26:52.333
Do you want to come
live with me in my vault?

26:55.416 --> 26:57.541
Yeah.

26:57.541 --> 26:59.500
Yeah, of course.

27:02.708 --> 27:04.250
[chuckles]

27:11.375 --> 27:13.875
[laughs]

27:15.958 --> 27:17.666
Let's go find that head.

27:26.000 --> 27:29.125
[DJ Carl] <i>Hey-yo, this Is DJ Carl at KPSS,</i>

27:29.125 --> 27:32.958
<i>broadcasting from the base
of the once-beautiful Hollywood Hills.</i>

27:32.958 --> 27:36.333
<i>Like most weeks here at KPSS,
this week is fiddle week,</i>

27:36.333 --> 27:39.375
<i>when all of my airtime
will be spent luxuriating</i>

27:39.375 --> 27:42.583
<i>in my small but mighty collection
of fiddle tunes.</i>

27:42.583 --> 27:44.625
<i>So, I'd encourage you to sit back</i>

27:44.625 --> 27:47.125
<i>and enjoy the folksy, gutsy sound</i>

27:47.125 --> 27:48.833
<i>of bygone fiddlers.</i>

27:48.833 --> 27:50.916
<i>And, if you don't like what you hear,</i>

27:50.916 --> 27:53.958
<i>just a reminder that
I don't take visitors at the station.</i>

27:53.958 --> 27:58.416
<i>A simple postcard will suffice.
That said, enjoy the fiddling.</i>

27:58.416 --> 28:00.500
<i>[gentle fiddle music playing]</i>

28:28.375 --> 28:30.375
[music continuing in distance]

28:42.916 --> 28:44.583
- Excuse me!
- Aah!

28:44.583 --> 28:47.458
Don't kill me. I'm a doctor.
I can help you.

28:51.625 --> 28:55.166
Haven't run into many people
traveling with a human head.

28:55.166 --> 28:58.250
Oh, this? It's not--
It's nothing really, it's more of a...

28:58.250 --> 29:00.833
I have to--
It's a souvenir kind of thing.

29:00.833 --> 29:01.958
Oh, yeah?

29:01.958 --> 29:04.750
Welcome to my humble pharmacy.

29:04.750 --> 29:06.666
- [grunts]
- [snake oil salesman] <i>Have a seat,
my dear boy,</i>

29:06.666 --> 29:09.041
and let's take a look at that

29:09.041 --> 29:11.291
tattered tootsy of yours.

29:14.333 --> 29:15.583
[groaning]

29:15.583 --> 29:17.291
[shuddering groans]

29:18.666 --> 29:20.875
Oh...

29:20.875 --> 29:23.125
Oh.

29:23.125 --> 29:24.458
I've seen this condition before.

29:24.458 --> 29:27.000
Uh, someone stepped on my foot.

29:27.000 --> 29:29.333
Yes. Sometimes fatal.

29:29.333 --> 29:31.791
But you're in luck,
'cause I've got the cure.

29:31.791 --> 29:34.833
I have, in my possession,
serums and potions

29:34.833 --> 29:36.916
for every malady and misfortune

29:36.916 --> 29:38.750
that could possibly beset

29:38.750 --> 29:40.333
a wandering traveler such as yourself.

29:42.166 --> 29:43.291
[hammer clicks]

29:50.583 --> 29:51.958
What's stopping me from just killing you

29:51.958 --> 29:53.916
and taking your whole thing of drugs?

29:53.916 --> 29:56.791
Well, when it comes to serums,

29:56.791 --> 29:58.208
not many people know the difference

29:58.208 --> 30:01.041
between the noxious and the benign.

30:01.041 --> 30:04.750
A murky hue of green could aid the humors.

30:04.750 --> 30:07.166
A brackish tint of shamrock, and...

30:07.166 --> 30:09.666
[blows raspberry]

30:09.666 --> 30:11.541
That's the sound of your lower intestine

30:11.541 --> 30:13.583
falling right the fuck out.

30:14.666 --> 30:16.916
But which is which?

30:16.916 --> 30:18.416
- Which is which--
- Fine.

30:18.416 --> 30:21.291
- Just give me the right one.
- Okay.

30:22.500 --> 30:25.625
Before we start,
there's the small matter of my fee.

30:28.125 --> 30:30.458
I don't have caps, but...

30:31.708 --> 30:33.500
[short chuckle]

30:33.500 --> 30:35.166
Oh, my.

30:35.166 --> 30:37.875
- Is-is that a...
- Fusion core?

30:39.000 --> 30:41.458
You don't see those around
much anymore, do you?

30:41.458 --> 30:42.875
[haunting music playing]

30:42.875 --> 30:45.583
But, if you do want to survive...

30:47.708 --> 30:49.458
...not a bad trade.

30:53.791 --> 30:56.250
Okay, here.

30:57.208 --> 30:59.791
Okay, let's get started.

31:11.833 --> 31:15.250
This elixir I have concocted heals all.

31:16.291 --> 31:18.375
And I mean everything.

31:18.375 --> 31:20.916
But I must warn you, the taste: not great.

31:20.916 --> 31:22.333
- Just give it.
- Okay.

31:24.750 --> 31:26.583
- [chuckles]
- [gags]

31:27.708 --> 31:29.125
[laughing] I'm sorry!

31:29.125 --> 31:31.041
[hacking cough]

31:31.041 --> 31:32.875
[laughs]

31:34.666 --> 31:36.250
But the results...

31:36.250 --> 31:38.791
Yes? The results.

31:45.250 --> 31:46.458
[Thaddeus gasps]

31:46.458 --> 31:48.958
Holy shit. Holy shit!

31:48.958 --> 31:50.750
Ah, thank you.

31:50.750 --> 31:53.416
- Sure thing, buddy boy.
- Ah...

31:54.875 --> 31:55.875
[case lock clicks]

31:55.875 --> 31:58.125
Do you know where
I can find a radio tower?

31:58.125 --> 32:00.333
I have to make contact with my base.

32:00.333 --> 32:02.666
Yes, I believe there's one yonward.

32:02.666 --> 32:05.333
Past the big crater
in the middle of the Shithole.

32:05.333 --> 32:07.958
It's near a town
that used to be called Shady Sands.

32:07.958 --> 32:09.500
Shady Sands?

32:09.500 --> 32:10.875
That place is radioactive as hell.

32:10.875 --> 32:14.083
Well, you don't have to worry about that
anymore, do you, buddy boy?

32:15.500 --> 32:18.833
Toodles and anon.

32:28.875 --> 32:30.875
[♪ Dinah Washington:
"What a Difference a Day Made"]

32:43.625 --> 32:46.208
<i>♪ What a difference ♪</i>

32:46.208 --> 32:48.791
<i>♪ A day made ♪</i>

32:51.708 --> 32:57.291
<i>♪ Twenty-four little hours ♪</i>

32:57.291 --> 32:58.333
[indistinct shouting]

32:59.666 --> 33:04.041
<i>♪ Brought the sun and the flowers ♪</i>

33:06.083 --> 33:07.250
<i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>

33:07.250 --> 33:10.416
<i>♪ Where there used to be rain...</i>

33:11.625 --> 33:13.083
[P.A. system chimes]

33:13.083 --> 33:14.250
[Reg] <i>Hello, Vault 33.</i>

33:14.250 --> 33:18.291
<i>In preparation for repopulating
our neighboring Vault 32,</i>

33:18.291 --> 33:21.916
<i>Overseer Betty will be sending out
vault assignments later today.</i>

33:21.916 --> 33:24.166
<i>Remember, wherever you end up,</i>

33:24.166 --> 33:26.541
<i>that's where you belong.</i>

33:30.125 --> 33:32.291
<i>♪ What a difference ♪</i>

33:32.291 --> 33:35.458
<i>♪ A day made ♪</i>

33:37.583 --> 33:40.250
<i>♪ And the difference ♪</i>

33:40.250 --> 33:42.750
<i>♪ Is you ♪</i>

33:43.958 --> 33:45.958
[sinister music playing]

33:51.333 --> 33:53.041
What happened?

33:53.041 --> 33:54.166
We don't know.

33:54.166 --> 33:56.625
The medic says it looks like rat poison.

33:56.625 --> 33:59.250
We'll find out who was behind it.

33:59.250 --> 34:00.791
Get off of me!

34:00.791 --> 34:03.666
I wouldn't---
I wouldn't do something like that!

34:03.666 --> 34:06.125
Ugh. More death.

34:06.125 --> 34:07.791
I wish it would end.

34:09.125 --> 34:11.625
What did I tell you, Norman?

34:13.000 --> 34:15.000
Words have meaning.

34:19.791 --> 34:22.375
People are gonna be upset
when they hear about this.

34:23.416 --> 34:26.458
People like to have
something to fuss about.

34:38.250 --> 34:39.958
[♪ Mozart: "Così fan tutte (overture)"
playing]

34:48.291 --> 34:49.625
Oh, fuck.

34:49.625 --> 34:51.708
- [Pip-Boys ding]
- Oh...

34:57.166 --> 34:58.833
[ding]

35:00.000 --> 35:01.166
Yes.

35:01.916 --> 35:03.458
[ding]

35:06.583 --> 35:08.291
[baby cries]

35:11.333 --> 35:13.333
- [sighs]
- [ding]

35:20.250 --> 35:21.541
[music ends]

35:30.041 --> 35:31.541
[latch clicks]

35:38.000 --> 35:39.500
Oh, hi, Norm.

35:39.500 --> 35:43.000
Oh, it-it's just terrible

35:43.000 --> 35:45.083
about the raiders, isn't it?

35:49.083 --> 35:50.375
Don't be too long.

35:50.375 --> 35:52.625
I'm holding the baby,
so you have to pack everything.

35:55.208 --> 35:57.125
We'll miss you, Norm.

35:58.125 --> 35:59.125
Hmm.

36:02.166 --> 36:03.750
You're going too?

36:03.750 --> 36:05.500
Yeah.

36:05.500 --> 36:08.125
Steph and I were given
a starter home unit.

36:08.125 --> 36:10.041
Just the three of us.

36:10.041 --> 36:11.458
Oh.

36:11.458 --> 36:14.250
So you're just gonna
forget about everything we've seen?

36:15.333 --> 36:18.666
I feel like this is a good moment
for a fresh start.

36:19.958 --> 36:21.291
You think so?

36:22.458 --> 36:24.000
Someone obviously does.

36:24.000 --> 36:25.458
Chet.

36:28.708 --> 36:30.750
You're a coward.

36:30.750 --> 36:32.625
You know that, Chet?

36:33.791 --> 36:34.958
[soft chuckles]

36:36.166 --> 36:37.791
We all are, Norm.

36:39.208 --> 36:41.375
That's why we live in a vault.

36:41.375 --> 36:43.458
[mournful music playing]

36:59.875 --> 37:01.875
[ominous music playing]

37:22.583 --> 37:24.583
♪ ♪

37:40.875 --> 37:42.458
[CX404 whimpering]

38:04.500 --> 38:06.083
[sighs]

38:07.125 --> 38:08.875
All right.

38:08.875 --> 38:11.041
Let's go find your daddy.

38:20.250 --> 38:23.333
- [♪ Cool Papa Jarvis: "Yeah Yeah Baby"]
- <i>♪ Baby ♪</i>

38:23.333 --> 38:27.041
<i>♪ Why you treat me like you do? ♪</i>

38:28.666 --> 38:32.291
<i>♪ Hey ♪</i>

38:32.291 --> 38:34.208
<i>♪ Baby ♪</i>

38:35.291 --> 38:38.708
<i>♪ Why you treat me like you do? ♪</i>

38:38.708 --> 38:40.791
[intriguing music playing]

39:01.625 --> 39:03.416
[short feedback]

39:05.000 --> 39:07.583
[Barb] I've got three hot cocoas on deck,

39:07.583 --> 39:10.500
two marshmallow, one plain.

39:10.500 --> 39:11.958
Three? You have one for me?

39:11.958 --> 39:14.250
- Yeah.
- Okay.

39:14.250 --> 39:15.708
I'll be out there in just a minute.

39:15.708 --> 39:17.125
Okay.

39:20.416 --> 39:22.208
[Barb sighs]

39:28.250 --> 39:29.958
[over earpiece] <i>Got your hot cocoa,
sweet pea.</i>

39:31.000 --> 39:32.833
<i>If you'd like,
you can have the marshmallows</i>

39:32.833 --> 39:34.166
<i>off of the top of mine.</i>

39:34.166 --> 39:35.333
[Janey] <i>Where's Daddy?</i>

39:35.333 --> 39:37.708
<i>He'll be out in a minute.</i>

39:37.708 --> 39:39.375
<i>- What've you got there?</i>
- [whimpers]

39:39.375 --> 39:41.791
<i>[conversation continues indistinctly]</i>

39:42.625 --> 39:43.958
[whines]

39:43.958 --> 39:45.416
<i>[both laughing]</i>

39:45.416 --> 39:47.625
You're right, Roosevelt.

39:49.166 --> 39:50.833
What are you thinking?

39:54.791 --> 39:56.791
[haunting music playing]

40:01.333 --> 40:04.000
[Cooper] <i>Lloyd and Cassandra here
are both scientists,</i>

40:04.000 --> 40:07.291
<i>specializing in the effects
of radiation on human DNA.</i>

40:07.291 --> 40:10.208
[Cassandra] <i>That's right,
and we'll be living and working</i>

40:10.208 --> 40:13.083
<i>right here in Vault 4, leading a community</i>

40:13.083 --> 40:15.041
<i>governed entirely by scientists.</i>

40:15.041 --> 40:17.166
<i>Well, I may be a hero in the movies,</i>

40:17.166 --> 40:19.625
<i>but you all are heroes in real life.</i>

40:22.625 --> 40:24.458
[sighs]

40:42.125 --> 40:44.791
No dogs in the vault, huh?

40:53.333 --> 40:54.541
[whines]

40:59.083 --> 41:01.083
♪ ♪

41:07.333 --> 41:09.125
[whines]

41:12.458 --> 41:15.666
I'm sorry, Dogmeat, but you ain't him.

41:15.666 --> 41:17.125
[whimpers]

41:18.458 --> 41:20.125
[sighs]

41:28.375 --> 41:30.375
[fiddle music playing]

41:38.791 --> 41:40.791
[music warbling over speakers]

41:50.083 --> 41:52.666
Yeah, my, uh, ride
should be getting here any minute.

41:52.666 --> 41:55.458
Thanks again for letting me
use your radio. That was really nice.

41:55.458 --> 41:57.333
Nah, no problem.

41:57.333 --> 41:59.250
[sighs]

42:00.541 --> 42:02.458
So, you were saying earlier
that some people,

42:02.458 --> 42:04.458
they don't, uh, like the sound
of this music, really?

42:04.458 --> 42:06.708
Oh, people get fully mad.

42:06.708 --> 42:08.666
- Oh.
- The thing no one appreciates is

42:08.666 --> 42:10.708
these are the original recordings.

42:10.708 --> 42:12.500
Oh. Uh-huh.

42:12.500 --> 42:14.791
You can't get that warm sound anymore.

42:14.791 --> 42:17.166
You know, the bass, the treble,

42:17.166 --> 42:19.208
the mids.

42:19.208 --> 42:20.583
Oh, that--

42:20.583 --> 42:22.750
Right, yeah. Oh.

42:22.750 --> 42:23.916
Here.

42:23.916 --> 42:25.625
Oh, that-- Okay, yeah.

42:27.250 --> 42:29.833
[chuckles] That's the, uh,
that's mids, right?

42:29.833 --> 42:31.333
- Yeah, yeah.
- Yeah.

42:31.333 --> 42:33.583
Wow, that's really got that

42:33.583 --> 42:35.041
- Yeah.
- thing on it.

42:35.041 --> 42:36.416
Well, it's not on it, it's in it.

42:36.416 --> 42:38.958
Oh, yeah, I like it. A lot, yeah.

42:38.958 --> 42:41.875
Some people,
they're just so ignorant to music,

42:41.875 --> 42:43.500
it's kind of sad, I would say.

42:43.500 --> 42:45.625
- Totally.
- Yep.

42:47.708 --> 42:50.250
Great job on these booby traps,
by the way.

42:50.250 --> 42:51.625
Really good.

42:51.625 --> 42:53.166
Hey, thanks.

42:59.166 --> 43:01.291
[Thaddeus sighs] Yeah.

43:01.291 --> 43:02.791
That one's crazy. [chuckles]

43:02.791 --> 43:05.333
[sighs] Critics.

43:07.916 --> 43:09.583
Yeah.

43:09.583 --> 43:13.291
People just, uh, can't be nice. [chuckles]

43:14.333 --> 43:15.375
Hey, is this your ride?

